Privacy Policy
1. Introduction

 

Welcome to ParentSwap! We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring you have a positive experience using our app. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information. By using ParentSwap, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

 

Company Information:

ParentSwap

Tweede Helmersstraat 30H

Amsterdam 1054CK

 

Contact Information:

Email: support@parentswap.app

 

2. Information We Collect

 

Personal Information:

 

• User email

• Phone number

• First and last name

• Birthdate

 

Child Profiles:

 

• Birthdate

• Photo

• First name

 

Family Picture:

 

• Collected for profile purposes.

 

Emergency Contacts:

 

• Information for safety and emergency purposes.

 

Home Address:

 

• Collected for verification and service provision.

 

ID Document Picture:

 

• For verification purposes.

 

3. How We Collect Information

 

We collect information from you in the following ways:

 

• During registration

• Through your use of the app

 

4. How We Use Your Information

 

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

 

• Service Provision: To provide and enhance our services.

• Safety: To ensure the safety of all users.

• Customization: To offer a personalized experience.

• Internal Marketing: We may use the data for internal marketing purposes.

• Third-Party Sharing: Data may be shared with third parties only for support purposes.

 

5. User Rights

 

Access and Correction:

You have the right to access and correct your personal data.

 

Deletion:

You can delete your data by contacting us at support@parentswap.app or through the app.

 

6. Data Security

 

We take the security of your data seriously and have implemented the following measures:

 

• We use servers and platforms that comply with SOC 2 and GDPR standards.

• Our security measures include automated code testing, vulnerability testing (including OWASP Top 10), and continuous monitoring technologies.

• ParentSwap is built on AWS, which supports 143 security standards and compliance certifications.

 

Data Retention:

We retain your data until you delete your account.

 

7. Cookies and Tracking

 

ParentSwap uses cookies and other tracking technologies to improve your experience. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.

 

8. Policy Updates

 

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Users will be informed about changes through updates in the app.

 

9. Children’s Privacy

 

ParentSwap is committed to protecting the privacy of children. Our app is intended for parents and guardians, and users must be at least 18 years old to register.

 

10. Compliance

 

ParentSwap complies with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and other relevant legal frameworks to protect your privacy and data rights.

 

If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy, please contact us at support@parentswap.app. Thank you for trusting ParentSwap with your information.
